column5: add-on::CV-Sunglass-Cases, Category:Accessories, cp-fall24, FALL-24, new-arrivals
column56: YUMA labs (the manufacturers we paired with to make our sunnies) are front-running in design and sustainability. Their products are made from high-quality materials and components (key for sustainability). They have a certified positive environmental impact and good social working conditions. Their products are all traceable throughout the supple chain, including a consumer-facing digital product passport. They prioritize circular design and all of their products are recyclable via their take-back program.
column58:
Frame Height -  59mm
Frame Width -  146mm
Lens Width -  55mm

The frames are crafted from bio acetate and acetate renew, which is made from eyewear production scraps that are collected, recycled and reuse. Includes 28% recycled content (of which is 50% post-consumer waste) and 42% to 68% bio-based content (wood or cotton fibers). This material has exactly the same quality as virgin acetate.

The lens is made from polycarbonate. This is a virgin material but it is recyclable.

The lenses are 100% UVA/UVB protection

The case is made from FSC certified paper 

The cleaning cloth is made from recycled PET plastic

Made in China

By entering the product code found on the inside of the arm of the sunglasses, you find the digital passport of your sunglasses - including all the information about them and the instructions to send them back to YUMA labs for recycling.

Includes 28% recycled content (of which is 50% post-consumer waste) and 42% to 68% bio-based content (wood or cotton fibers). This material has exactly the same quality as virgin acetate.

The lens is made from polycarbonate. This is a virgin material but it is recyclable.

The lenses are 100% UVA/UVB protection

The case is made from FSC certified paper 

The cleaning cloth is made from recycled PET plastic

Made in China

By entering the product code found on the inside of the arm of the sunglasses, you find the digital passport of your sunglasses - including all the information about them and the instructions to send them back to YUMA labs for recycling.
